HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 141
BY REPRESENTATIVE HILFERTY
A RESOLUTION
To commend Joseph Giarrusso, III, for his service to New Orleans City Council District A.
WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Joseph Giarrusso, III, for his civic
leadership and to commend him for his service to New Orleans City Council District A; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Giarrusso dedicated eight years of service as the councilman
representing New Orleans City Council District A, and he previously served as president of
the Lakeview Civic Improvement Association; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Giarrusso served as New Orleans City Council's budget chair,
where he managed the city's finances, saved taxpayers hundreds of millions of dollars, and
protected vital public services; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Giarrusso's service was defined by his leadership, accessibility, and
commitment to fairness; he left an indelible mark on the Lakeview community and all of
District A; and
WHEREAS, Joseph Giarrusso, III, is most deserving of the highest recognition for
his integrity, vision, and devotion to the community he served.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend Joseph Giarrusso, III, for his service to New
Orleans City Council District A and does hereby extend sincere wishes that he remains
prosperous in his new role as first deputy mayor and chief administrative officer of the City
of New Orleans.
SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
